# Gmail (for syncing emails → network bubbles)
# 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 2. Create project → APIs & Services → Credentials → Create OAuth 2.0 Client ID
# 3. Application type: Web application
# 4. Authorized JavaScript origins: http://localhost:5173 (or your dev port)
# 5. Enable Gmail API in APIs & Services → Library
# 6. Copy "Client ID" below
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=

# Outlook (optional)
# Azure Portal → App registrations → SPA platform, Mail.Read permission
VITE_AZURE_CLIENT_ID=
VITE_AZURE_TENANT_ID=common
